			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<strong>Job summary</strong><br />
	This is your chance to join a young and dynamic company and make a big impact. The Digital Designer will join a higly skilled and enthusiastic team responsible for the design, including specification, design, verification, of digital and mixed signal microcontroller products.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Key responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Work in teams with design- and verification engineers</li>
	<li>
		Specification, design, verification, of digital and mixed signal microcontroller and radio transceiver products.</li>
	<li>
		Top-level (system) specification, design and verification</li>
	<li>
		Digital signal processing</li>
	<li>
		Specify and develop test plans for modules and systems</li>
	<li>
		Methodology development (Low Power Digital Design)</li>
	<li>
		Synthesis</li>
	<li>
		Technical documentation</li>
	<li>
		Silicon validation and debug</li>
	<li>
		Project management</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		B.S., M.S. or Ph.D in Electrical Engineering or equivalent experience is required</li>
	<li>
		3-10 years experience with design and verification of digital and SoC systems</li>
	<li>
		Juniors (0-2 years of experience) with outstanding results from university may also be considered</li>
	<li>
		Some experience with analog and mixed-signal systems is an advantage</li>
	<li>
		Experience with low power design is an advantage</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Personal profile</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		You have most of the following personal qualities</li>
	<li>
		Enthusiastic and creative</li>
	<li>
		Good analytical and system troubleshooting skills</li>
	<li>
		Good written and oral communication skills</li>
	<li>
		Team player</li>
</ul>
